### ============================================================
### CORRECT Co-op Integration Workflow
###
### This file shows the CORRECT way to test Co-op integration:
### 1. Call backend /stk-push → creates payment record
### 2. Use the messageRef from step 1 in callback simulation
###
### WRONG approach (what you were doing):
###   - Sending STK push directly to Co-op (bypasses backend)
###   - Using random messageRefs in callbacks
###   - Result: "Payment not found" error
###
### CORRECT approach (this file):
###   - Call backend endpoint → creates DB record
###   - Use the SAME messageRef in callback
###   - Result: Payment is properly tracked end-to-end
### ============================================================

### Setup: Log in first
POST {{api_url}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@jaytechwavesolutions.co.ke",
  "password": "Michira._2000"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        const body = JSON.parse(response.body);
        const token = body.data.token;
        client.global.set("auth_token", token);
        client.log("✓ Logged in as benjamin@example.com");
        client.log("  Token: " + token.substring(0, 30) + "...");
    } else {
        client.log("✗ Login failed: " + response.status);
        client.log("Response: " + response.body);
    }
%}

###

### ============================================================
### STEP 1: Initiate STK Push via Backend
###
### This is the CORRECT starting point.
### Backend will:
###   1. Generate a unique messageRef
###   2. Create a payment record in DB
###   3. Call Co-op API with this messageRef
###   4. Return the messageRef to you
###
### Status: ✅ Creates payment record in DB
### ============================================================
POST {{api_url}}/api/v1/payments/stk-push
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "phoneNumber": "254716962489",
  "amount": 1.00,
  "accountReference": "BENJAMIN-STK-TEST"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        const body = JSON.parse(response.body);
        const messageRef = body.data.messageReference;
        const message = body.data.message;

        client.global.set("test_message_reference", messageRef);
        client.global.set("stk_push_response", response.body);

        client.log("✓ STK Push initiated via backend");
        client.log("  MessageReference: " + messageRef);
        client.log("  Message: " + message);
        client.log("  ⚠️ SAVE THIS MessageReference - you'll use it in the next step!");
    } else {
        client.log("✗ STK push initiation failed: " + response.status);
        client.log("Response: " + response.body);
    }
%}

###

### ============================================================
### STEP 2: Simulate Callback with MATCHING MessageReference
###
### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Use the SAME messageRef from Step 1
###
### Co-op will eventually post to /coop/stk-callback with:
###   - MessageReference: (the one you just got)
###   - TransactionID: (their transaction ID)
###   - MessageCode: "0" for success
###
### This simulation lets you test without waiting for real Co-op
### Status: ✅ Matches payment record from Step 1
### ============================================================
POST {{api_url}}/api/v1/payments/coop/stk-callback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "MessageReference": "{{test_message_reference}}",
  "MessageCode": "0",
  "MessageDescription": "The service request is processed successfully.",
  "Amount": "1.00",
  "TransactionID": "COOP_{{$timestamp}}_{{$randomInt(10000, 99999)}}",
  "MobileNumber": "254712345678",
  "OperatorCode": "BETTERLINK"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        const body = JSON.parse(response.body);
        client.log("✓ Callback processed successfully!");
        client.log("  MessageCode: " + body.MessageCode);
        client.log("  Message: " + body.Message);
        client.log("");
        client.log("✓ Verify in database:");
        client.log("  SELECT * FROM payments WHERE internal_ref = '{{test_message_reference}}';");
        client.log("  Status should be: COMPLETED");
    } else {
        client.log("✗ Callback processing failed: " + response.status);
        client.log("Response: " + response.body);
    }
%}

###

### ============================================================
### STEP 3: Verify Payment in Database
###
### After running Steps 1-2, check that the payment was created
### and updated correctly
### ============================================================
GET {{api_url}}/api/v1/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        const body = JSON.parse(response.body);
        const payments = body.data;

        client.log("✓ Recent payments:");
        payments.forEach(p => {
            client.log("  - Ref: " + p.internalRef + " | Status: " + p.status + " | Amount: " + p.amount);
        });
    } else {
        client.log("✗ Failed to fetch payments: " + response.status);
    }
%}

###

### ============================================================
### TROUBLESHOOTING
### ============================================================
###
### If you get "Payment not found for MessageReference: X"
###
### Causes:
###   1. ❌ Using a messageRef that wasn't created by backend
###   2. ❌ Sending STK push directly to Co-op (bypasses backend)
###   3. ❌ Using a different messageRef in callback than in STK push
###
### Solution:
###   ✅ Always start with Step 1 (backend /stk-push endpoint)
###   ✅ Copy the messageRef from the response
###   ✅ Use that SAME messageRef in all subsequent callbacks
###
### ============================================================

